<Issue id="15829" key="INDY-2" number="2" project="10303" reporter="stevetolman" assignee="stevetolman" creator="stevetolman" type="10004" summary="How to log a good Indy bug" environment="Include OS, Indy platform version, and specific configuration settings that may prove useful." priority="3" resolution="10000" status="10001" created="2017-04-19 02:42:52.0" updated="2019-10-09 09:39:18.0" resolutiondate="2019-10-09 09:39:18.0" votes="0" watches="1" workflowId="16708"> <description><! CDATA Include a crisp and concise summary.  Ensure the Issue is unique. Please check existing issues to see if the issue is already logged.  If not then log a new ticket that includes the following.  In the description field (this field) include: - Short but descriptive title - Comprehensive description including: -- Build number -- Steps to Reproduce  In the various appropriate Jira fields include: - Environment and configuration - Attachment(s)/evidence/artifacts -- Log files that show info about the issue (errors, warnings, etc.) -- Screen shots -- Code snippets where applicable - In the Linked Issues field, please define how this ticket affects other tickets, if at all - Priority -- Leave blank for medium priority -- For consistency, please follow the chart below as much as possible   ||Severity||Ticket Priority|| | Hang, Data loss, Security holes | Highest | | Broken - Unusable or difficult workaround | High | | Broken - easy workaround | Medium | | Annoyance | Low |   Please do NOT include: - Opinions or editorials  ></description> </Issue>
